*Q) What is accessibility?*

A) Accessibility is a set of standardized practices that ensures your code meets 100% test coverage.  
B) Accessibility is a set of standardized practices that enhances the speed and performance for your web applications.  
C) Accessibility is a set of standardized practices that ensures your code is free from all security risks.  
D) Accessibility is a set of standardized practices to ensure your web applications can be used by everyone, including those with disabilities.  

> [!question]- Answer  
> **D) Accessibility is a set of standardized practices to ensure your web applications can be used by everyone, including those with disabilities.**  

---

*Q) Which of the following is a good example for proper heading level structure?*

A) 
```html
<h6>Heading 6</h6>
<h5>Heading 5</h5>
<h4>Heading 4</h4>
<h3>Heading 3</h3>
<h2>Heading 2</h2>
<h1>Heading 1</h1>
```
B)
```html
<h6>Heading 6</h6>

<h1>Heading 1</h1>
<h1>Heading 1</h1>

<h5>Heading 5</h5>

<h2>Heading 2</h2>
<h2>Heading 2</h2>
```
C)
```html
<h1>Heading 1</h1>
<h2>Heading 2</h2>
<h3>Heading 3</h3>
<h4>Heading 4</h4>
<h5>Heading 5</h5>
<h6>Heading 6</h6>
```
D)
```html
<h3>Heading 3</h3>
<h3>Heading 3</h3>
<h3>Heading 3</h3>

<h1>Heading 1</h1>
<h2>Heading 2</h2>
<h4>Heading 4</h4>
```

> [!question]- Answer  
> **D)**

---

*Q) What are the six main categories of ARIA roles?*

A) Window, Alert Dialog, Article, Cell, Banner, and Button.  
B) Document Structure, Landmark, Window, Abstract, Widget, and Live Region.  
C) Document Structure, Landmark, Window, Explicit, Fidget, and Footer.  
D) Landmark, House, Live Region, Application, Window, and Extension.  

> [!question]- Answer  
> **B) Document Structure, Landmark, Window, Abstract, Widget, and Live Region.**  

---

*Q) What is the correct way to add an alt attribute to an <img> tag?*

A)
```html
alt="cat running"<img src="cat.jpg">
```
B)
```html
alt=""<img src="cat.jpg">
```
C)
```html
<img src="cat.jpg"> alt="cat running"
```
D)
```html
<img src="cat.jpg" alt="cat running">  
```

> [!question]- Answer  
> **D) <img src="cat.jpg" alt="cat running">**  

---

*Q) What does WAI-ARIA stand for?*

A) Web Anchor Initiative - Anchor Rich Internet Applications.  
B) Website Accessible Initiative - Accessible Rust Internet Applications.  
C) Web Accessibility Initial - Accessible Ready Internet Applications.  
D) Web Accessibility Initiative - Accessible Rich Internet Applications.  

> [!question]- Answer  
> **D) Web Accessibility Initiative - Accessible Rich Internet Applications.**  

---

*Q) What is the role of the aria-hidden attribute?*

A) This attribute is used to hide an element from assistive technologies.  
B) This attribute is used to hide an element only to keyboard users.  
C) This attribute is used to hide elements only for users with visual impairments.  
D) This attribute is used to hide and add label text for an element.  

> [!question]- Answer  
> **A) This attribute is used to hide an element from assistive technologies.**  

---

*Q) Which attribute makes elements focusable and defines the relative order in which they are navigated using the keyboard?*

A) tabindex  
B) tabbingindex  
C) indextab  
D) keyboardindex  

> [!question]- Answer  
> **A) tabindex.**  

---

*Q) Why is it a good practice to include the caption element inside an HTML table?*

A) It helps improve the table's responsiveness on mobile devices.  
B) It enhances the table's appearance by adding a decorative header.  
C) It is helpful for users to quickly understand the table's purpose and content.  
D) It allows users to easily sort and filter the table's data.  

> [!question]- Answer  
> **C) It is helpful for users to quickly understand the table's purpose and content.**  

---

*Q) What is the difference between the attributes aria-label and aria-labelledby?*

A) The aria-label attribute is used to give a color to its label while the aria-labelledby attribute is used to give height to its label.  
B) The aria-label and aria-labelledby attributes keep labels undefined.  
C) The aria-label and aria-labelledby attributes serve the same purpose.  
D) The aria-labelledby attribute allows you to give an element an accessible name by referencing an existing element on the page while the aria-label attribute allows you to define the name in the attribute itself.  

> [!question]- Answer  
> **D) The aria-labelledby attribute allows you to give an element an accessible name by referencing an existing element on the page while the aria-label attribute allows you to define the name in the attribute itself.**  

---

*Q) Which of the following ARIA states is used to indicate that an element is selected?*

A) aria-expanded  
B) aria-label  
C) aria-haspopup  
D) aria-selected  

> [!question]- Answer  
> **D) aria-selected.**  

---

*Q) Which of the following is NOT a common ARIA state?*

A) aria-hidden  
B) aria-disabled  
C) aria-columns  
D) aria-checked  

> [!question]- Answer  
> **C) aria-columns.**  

---

*Q) Which of the following examples is the correct way to associate a label with an input element?*

A) 
```html
<form>
   <label for="name">Your Name</label>
   <input type="text" id="name" />
</form>
```
B)
```html
<form>
   <label accessible="name">Your Name</label>
   <input type="text" id="name" />
</form>
```
C)
```html
<form>
   <label associate="name">Your Name</label>
   <input type="text" id="name" />
</form>
```
D)
```html
<form>
   <label for="name">Your Name</label>
   <input type="text" id="first-name" />
</form>
```

> [!question]- Answer  
> **A)**  

---

*Q) How does a screen magnifier help visually-impaired users navigate web pages?*

A) A screen magnifier will enlarge only images to twice their size so they can be better viewed by visually-impaired users.  
B) A screen magnifier helps visually-impaired users navigate web pages by allowing them to zoom in and out.  
C) A screen magnifier converts text to Braille for tactile reading.  
D) A screen magnifier automatically adjusts the color contrast of web pages.  

> [!question]- Answer  
> **B) A screen magnifier helps visually-impaired users navigate web pages by allowing them to zoom in and out.**  

---

*Q) What is the role of the aria-haspopup attribute?*

A) To indicate that an element can trigger a popup like a menu or dialog.  
B) To indicate that an element has keyboard shortcuts associated with it.  
C) To indicate that an element has a tooltip associated with it.  
D) To specify the language of the element's content.  

> [!question]- Answer  
> **A) To indicate that an element can trigger a popup like a menu or dialog.**  

---

*Q) Which of the following is NOT a commonly used ARIA role?*

A) role="access"  
B) role="tab"  
C) role="alert"  
D) role="menu"  

> [!question]- Answer  
> **A) role="access".**  

---

*Q) Which of the following attributes is used to create a live region on your page which can be used to notify screen reader users of dynamic content changes?*

A) aria-live  
B) aria-label  
C) aria-region  
D) aria-expanded  

> [!question]- Answer  
> **A) aria-live.**  

---

*Q) What is the purpose of the role attribute?*

A) To style elements with CSS animations allowing assistive technologies to better understand how the element should be interpreted and interacted with.  
B) To add labels to form elements allowing assistive technologies to better understand how the element should be interpreted and interacted with.  
C) To define the visual appearance of HTML elements allowing assistive technologies to better understand how the element should be interpreted and interacted with.  
D) To specify the type and purpose of an element, allowing assistive technologies to better understand how the element should be interpreted and interacted with.  

> [!question]- Answer  
> **D) To specify the type and purpose of an element, allowing assistive technologies to better understand how the element should be interpreted and interacted with.**  

---

*Q) Why is it important to use descriptive link text for links?*

A) To ensure the link loads faster when clicked.  
B) To ensure that search engines will always list your site as the first result in the list.  
C) To make the link text stand out visually from the rest of the page content.  
D) To ensure that everyone, including users of assistive technology understand the purpose of the link.  

> [!question]- Answer  
> **D) To ensure that everyone, including users of assistive technology understand the purpose of the link.**  

---

*Q) Which of the following is a best practice for making audio and video content accessible?*

A) Providing high-quality graphics to accompany the audio and video content to make it accessible to people with visual impairments.  
B) Limiting the length of audio and video content to make it accessible to people with hearing impairments.  
C) Providing captions and transcripts for audio and video content to make it accessible to people with hearing impairments.  
D) Using bright colors and large text to make the content more engaging and to make it accessible to people with visual impairments.  

> [!question]- Answer  
> **C) Providing captions and transcripts for audio and video content to make it accessible to people with hearing impairments.**  

---

*Q) Which of the following attributes is used to indicate that an element is in the checked state?*

A) aria-checked  
B) aria-ischecked  
C) aria-checking  
D) aria-checkbox  

> [!question]- Answer  
> **A) aria-checked.**  

